name: eqneltrd
params: class c0, class c1, class c2, wff w0

body.origin:
|- wi(w0, wn(wcel(c0, c1)))
-| wi(w0, wn(wcel(c2, c1)))
-| wi(w0, wb(wcel(c0, c1), wcel(c2, c1)))

cumulated.origin:
|- wi(w0, wn(wcel(c0, c1)))
-| wi(w0, wn(wcel(c2, c1)))
-| wi(w0, wb(wcel(c0, c1), wcel(c2, c1)))

body.origin:
|- wi(w0, wb(wcel(c0, c1), wcel(c2, c1)))
-| wi(w0, wceq(c0, c2))

cumulated.origin:
|- wi(w0, wn(wcel(c0, c1)))
-| wi(w0, wn(wcel(c2, c1)))
-| wi(w0, wceq(c0, c2))

comment: If a class is not an element of another class, an equal class is also not an element. Deduction form. (Contributed by David Moews, 1-May-2017.)
